Heat tree

  • metacoder package
  • paper : Foster, Z. S., Sharpton, T. J., & Grnwald, N. J. (2017). Metacoder: An R package for visualization and manipulation of community taxonomic diversity data. PLoS computational biology, 13(2), e1005404. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1005404

library(phyloseq)
library(metacoder)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

01.import data

ps <- readRDS("./ps.rds") %>%
  transform_sample_counts(function(x) x/sum(x) ) %>% 
  subset_samples(body.site %in% c("gut", "tongue"))
ps # 770 taxa and 17 samples
## phyloseq-class experiment-level object
## otu_table()   OTU Table:         [ 770 taxa and 17 samples ]
## sample_data() Sample Data:       [ 17 samples by 8 sample variables ]
## tax_table()   Taxonomy Table:    [ 770 taxa by 7 taxonomic ranks ]
## phy_tree()    Phylogenetic Tree: [ 770 tips and 768 internal nodes ]
# read 0 , taxa
ps.f = prune_samples(sample_sums(ps)>0, ps) 
# ps.f = prune_taxa(rowSums(otu_table(t(ps.f))) > 0, ps.f) #

02.phylsoeq to metacoder object

obj <- parse_phyloseq(ps.f)
  • abundance and difference calculation
obj$data$tax_data <- calc_obs_props(obj, "tax_data") #  taxa 
obj$data$tax_abund <- calc_taxon_abund(obj, "otu_table") #  abundance 
obj$data$tax_occ <- calc_n_samples(obj, "tax_abund", 
                                   groups = obj$data$sample_data$body.site, 
                                   cols = obj$data$sample_data$sample_id)

obj$data$diff_table <- compare_groups(obj, data = "tax_abund",  # wilcoxon rank sum test
                                      cols = obj$data$sample_data$sample_id,
                                      groups = obj$data$sample_data$body.site)
print(obj$data$diff_table)

03. draw heat tree

obj %>% 
  filter_taxa(taxon_ranks == "Genus", supertaxa = TRUE) %>% 
  heat_tree(node_label = taxon_names,
            node_size_axis_label = "Number of ASVs",
            node_size = n_obs,
            node_color_axis_label = "Mean difference",
            node_color = mean_diff,
            node_color_range= c("#E31A1C","grey90",  "#1F78B4"), 
            layout = "davidson-harel", 
            initial_layout = "reingold-tilford",
            output_file = "./heat_tree_ex1.pdf")

obj %>% 
  filter_taxa(taxon_ranks == "Genus", supertaxa = TRUE) %>% 
  heat_tree(node_label = taxon_names,
            node_size_axis_label = "Number of ASVs",
            node_size = n_obs,
            node_color_axis_label = "Mean difference",
            node_color = mean_diff,
            node_color_range= c("#E31A1C","grey90",  "#1F78B4"), 
            output_file = "./heat_tree_ex2.pdf")

DESeq2 test

ps <- readRDS("./ps.rds") %>%
  subset_samples(body.site %in% c("gut", "tongue")) # Not relative abundance
ps.f = prune_samples(sample_sums(ps)>0, ps) 


obj2 = parse_phyloseq(ps.f)


obj2$data$tax_data <- calc_obs_props(obj2, "tax_data") #  taxa 
obj2$data$tax_abund <- calc_taxon_abund(obj2, "otu_table") #  abundance 
obj2$data$tax_occ <- calc_n_samples(obj2, "tax_abund", 
                                   groups = obj2$data$sample_data$body.site, 
                                   cols = obj$data$sample_data$sample_id)

  filter_taxa(taxon_ranks == "Genus", supertaxa = TRUE) %>% 
  heat_tree(node_label = taxon_names,
            node_size = n_obs,
            node_color_axis_label = "Log2 fold change",
            node_size_axis_label = "Number of ASVs",
            node_color = ifelse(is.na(padj) | padj > 0.05, 0, log2FoldChange),
            node_color_range= c("#E31A1C","grey90",  "#1F78B4"), 
            layout = "davidson-harel", 
            initial_layout = "reingold-tilford",
            output_file = "./heat_tree_ex3.pdf")
